     <body>
     <div type="poem">
   <pb facs="8"/>
   <head>ON THE SEVEN DAYES.</head>
   <l>THe glorious <hi>God</hi> the <hi>First Day</hi> made the <hi>Light:</hi>
   </l>
   <l>
      <hi>Next</hi> stretcht the <hi>Firmament</hi> in bredth &amp; hight:</l>
   <l>The <hi>Third</hi> dryde <hi>Earth,</hi> and it with Plants He stor'd:</l>
   <l>The <hi>Fourth</hi> the <hi>Heauens</hi> with Lamps of light decor'd:</l>
   <l>
      <hi>Fift</hi> th'Aire with Fowls, with Fishes filde each Flood:</l>
   <l>The <hi>Sixt</hi> made <hi>Beasts</hi> and <hi>Man:</hi> and all were good.</l>
   <l>On the <hi>Seuenth Day</hi> the <hi>Lord</hi> from worke did rest;</l>
   <l>Therefore that <hi>Day</hi> Hee sanctifi'd and blest.</l>
   <bibl>
      <hi>I. A.</hi>
   </bibl>
</div>
